The paper focuses on network pruning for deep model compression, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves selecting channels/kernels based on their discriminative power, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adaptive stopping conditions, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
